# SAS 9.4 License Renewal — Intune Deployment Script

A PowerShell script for silently renewing an existing SAS 9.4 license via Microsoft Intune. No reinstallation required — copies a new license file, runs SAS Deployment Manager silently, and writes a registry key so Intune knows the renewal succeeded.

---

## Overview

SAS 9.4 Teaching & Research licenses expire annually. Manually renewing across a fleet of managed endpoints is time-consuming and requires users to have elevated privileges they typically don't have. This script packages the entire renewal workflow into a single Intune-deployable unit.

**What it does:**
- Checks for an active user session before proceeding (defers if no user is present — Intune retries automatically)
- Notifies the user that a license check is taking place
- Validates that SAS 9.4 is actually installed before attempting renewal
- Checks the registry to see if the license is already current (skips renewal if so, still writes detection key)
- Copies the new license file and response file from the Intune package to a local working directory
- Gracefully closes any running SAS processes with a 30-second user warning
- Runs SAS Deployment Manager silently using a pre-configured response file
- Writes a registry detection key so Intune reports the device as compliant
- Logs everything locally and optionally to a network share
- Writes key events to the Windows Event Log for monitoring visibility

