## Configuration

At the top of `Renewal_SAS_2026.ps1`, update the `$Config` hashtable for your environment:

```powershell
$LicenseYear = "2026"   # Update each renewal cycle

$Config = @{
    LicenseFileName    = "SAS_94_TR_${LicenseYear}_License.txt"
    LicenseDestination = "C:\ProgramData\...\SAS"        # Local working directory
    LogsRootNetwork    = "\\...\Share\IT\...\Logs\SAS_Renewal_${LicenseYear}_Logs"
    LogsRootLocal      = "C:\Intune_Logs\SAS_Renewal_${LicenseYear}_Logs"
    RegistryPath       = "HKLM:\Software\...\SAS"        # Intune detection key location
    RegistryValueName  = "LicenseYear"
    EventLogSource     = "SAS-Renewal"
}
```

### Response file

The `SAS_Renewal_2026.properties` file must point to the license file at the **local working directory path**, not a network share — it runs after files are copied locally:

```properties
INSTALLER_UI=silent
SAS_INSTALLATION_DATA=C:\ProgramData\...\SAS\SAS_94_TR_2026_License.txt
QUIET_MODE=true
```

