## How It Works

```
Intune triggers script as SYSTEM
        │
        ▼
Is an active user session present?
   No  → Exit 2 (Intune retries on next check-in)
   Yes ↓
        │
        ▼
Notify user: license check in progress
        │
        ▼
Is SAS 9.4 installed?
   No  → Exit 1 (not a renewal candidate)
   Yes ↓
        │
        ▼
Is license already current year?
   Yes → Write registry key, exit 0
   No  ↓
        │
        ▼
Copy license + response file from Intune package → local working directory
        │
        ▼
Are SAS processes running?
   Yes → Warn user (30-second countdown), gracefully close, force if needed
   No  ↓
        │
        ▼
Run sasdm.exe silently with response file
        │
        ▼
Write registry detection key
        │
        ▼
Notify user: renewal complete, log result, exit 0
```

