## Logging

The script writes to three locations:

- **Local log:** `C:\Intune_Logs\SAS_Renewal_2026_Logs\`
- **Network log:** `\\...\Logs\SAS_Renewal_2026_Logs\` *(falls back gracefully if unavailable)*
- **Windows Event Log:** Application log, source `SAS-Renewal`

Event IDs written:

| ID | Event |
|---|---|
| 1000 | Script started |
| 1001 | Renewal completed successfully |
| 1002 | Renewal failed |
| 1003 | Deferred — no active user session |
| 1004 | Logging initialization failed |
| 1005 | Network logging unavailable |
| 1006 | Unhandled exception |

Query from PowerShell:
```powershell
Get-WinEvent -FilterHashtable @{LogName='Application'; ProviderName='SAS-Renewal'}
```

